fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IPageGuard


  • public interface IPageGuard
    Defines collections of paths that are guarded by authentication services. Also defines exclusions, the authentication mode (such as "auto" or "password"), and (depending upon mode) the authentication design.

    When a password-based page guard has access to an instance of IPlatformAuthnService, it automatically enables use of one-time passwords. The URIs for form-based and one-time password-based authentication may be configurable.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

        static final String INITIAL_URI_KEY

      • isUsingSpecificAuthnServices

        boolean isUsingSpecificAuthnServices()
        Indicates if this page guard uses only specific authentication services, or if it uses any suitable and available service.

        Note: when this returns false, it is expected that getAuthnServiceIds() should return an empty list.

        Returns:
        true if a non-default restrictive configuration is defined, limiting the configuration services that can be used, or false (the default) if any available instance of IPasswordAuthnService can be used.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getAuthnServiceIds(), isAutoAuthn(), isPasswordAuthn()

      • getAuthnServiceIds

        Set<UUID> getAuthnServiceIds()
        Identifies specific authentication services that this page guard will use, if restricted. By default, this returns an empty list as any available instance of IPasswordAuthnService can be used.

        Note: this should only return a non-empty list when isUsingSpecificAuthnServices() returns true.

        Returns:
        a list of specific authentication services that can be used by this page guard, or an empty list (the default) if any compatible authentication service can be used. Should never return null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        isUsingSpecificAuthnServices(), isAutoAuthn(), isPasswordAuthn()

      • getInclusivePaths

        List<String> getInclusivePaths()
        Gets the list of paths that are protected by this page guard. A list of exceptions can also be defined, so that specific subpaths of a protected path can be excluded (for example, it may be desirable to exclude a "/media/" path), in addition to rule-based predicates.
        Returns:
        a non-null list of literal paths, each starting and ending with a "/" character, with no pattern matching. Any call to the application using a path starting with one of these inclusive paths is considered as protected by this page guard.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getExclusivePaths

        List<String> getExclusivePaths()
        Gets the list of paths that are excluded from protection by this page guard. The list of excluded paths is compared with the set of included paths for this page guard. It is not necessary to specify paths that are not protected by this page guard (they will be ignored).
        Returns:
        a non-null list of literal paths, each starting and ending with a "/" character, with no pattern matching. Any path that matches one of this page guard's inclusive paths will be checked against this set.
        Since:
        1.0

      • isPasswordAuthn

        boolean isPasswordAuthn()
        Indicates if this page guard uses password-based authentication in order to make protected content available. If passwords-based authentication is used, then an associated page design is also required.
        Returns:
        true if this page guard uses passwords provided by the end user, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getPasswordAuthnDesign()

      • getPasswordAuthnDesign

        IPasswordAuthnDesign getPasswordAuthnDesign()
        Gets the password authentication design associated with this page guard, if it uses password-based authentication.
        Returns:
        the associated design, or null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        isPasswordAuthn()

      • isAutoAuthn

        boolean isAutoAuthn()
        Indicates if this page guard uses automatic authentication, capable of providing tickets without user interaction when processing an HTTP request. Examples include public content (with an implicit user), and single sign-on authentication systems using call properties (address segments, cookies, or other headers).
        Returns:
        true if this page guard uses automatic authentication, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getAuthnServiceIds()
